BTTTriggers.BTTPredefinedActionName: Run Apple Script (enter directly as text)
BTTTriggers.BTTInlineAppleScript: on replace_chars(this_text, search_string, replacement_string)	if this_text contains the search_string then		set AppleScript's text item delimiters to the search_string		set the item_list to every text item of this_text		set AppleScript's text item delimiters to the replacement_string		set this_text to the item_list as string		set AppleScript's text item delimiters to ""	end if	return this_textend replace_chars-- Fetch resultset percentChange to do shell script "curl -s 'https://api.coinmarketcap.com/v1/ticker/neo/' | grep 'percent_change_1h'"-- Clean up resultset percentChange to replace_chars(percentChange, "        \"percent_change_1h\": \"", "")set percentChange to replace_chars(percentChange, "\", ", "")-- Display resultreturn percentChange & "%"

BTTTriggerConfig.BTTTouchBarAppleScriptString: on replace_chars(this_text, search_string, replacement_string)	if this_text contains the search_string then		set AppleScript's text item delimiters to the search_string		set the item_list to every text item of this_text		set AppleScript's text item delimiters to the replacement_string		set this_text to the item_list as string		set AppleScript's text item delimiters to ""	end if	return this_textend replace_chars-- Fetch resultset stockValue to do shell script "curl -s 'https://api.coinmarketcap.com/v1/ticker/neo/?convert=AUD' | grep 'price_aud'"-- Clean up resultset stockValue to replace_chars(stockValue, "        \"price_aud\": \"", "")set stockValue to replace_chars(stockValue, "\", ", "")-- Set to 2 decimalsset stockValue to stockValue * 100set stockValue to round stockValueset stockValue to stockValue / 100-- Display resultreturn "$" & stockValue
